com.braze

Class BrazeUser

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.appboy.AppboyUser
      • com.braze.BrazeUser

  • public class BrazeUser
extends AppboyUser
    BrazeUser provides an object which lets you update the attributes stored by Braze for your user.

    This class has been designed to provide fire and forget semantics and to not impact the performance or lifecycle of calling code. As such, in the case of any Exception, all class methods catch and log the error, and then return false. Some methods also enforce input validation, the rules of which are documented on the individual method.

    Changes made to an BrazeUser are persisted using SharedPreferences storage until they are persisted to Braze servers. In all supported Android versions, writing to SharedPreferences is performed asynchronously.
